Executive Profile
Robert D. Daleo  Independent Director, Equifax Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships67$260,996
Background

		Mr. Robert D. Daleo, also known as Bob served as Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President at Thomson Reuters Corporation (formerly The Thomson Corp and Selkirk Financial Technologies, Inc.) from November 1998 to January 1, 2012. Mr. Daleo served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Thomson Scientific & Healthcare, Healthcare Magazines. Mr. Daleo began his career with The Thomson Corporation in January 1994 when he joined Thomson Newspapers ... as Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer. Since 1996, he served as a Chief Operating Officer of Thomson Newspapers and was responsible for a significant portion of its United States operations. At the beginning of 1997, he joined Thomson Corporate as Senior Vice President of Finance and Business Development and also served as its Executive Vice President of Business Operations and Planning. Prior to joining The Thomson Corporation, he served various financial and operations positions with McGraw-Hill and Automatic Data Processing. He serves as Chairman of the New Jersey Community Development Corporation. He served as a Vice Chairman of Thomson Reuters Corporation since January 1, 2012 and served as its Director since 2001. He has been a Director of Citrix Systems, Inc. since May 10, 2013. Mr. Daleo has been an Independent Director of Equifax Inc. since August 7, 2006. He serves as a Director of Healthcare Magazines. He served as a Director of Thomson Scientific & Healthcare, Healthcare Magazines. He is a Member of Northwestern Mutual Insurance Company's Policyowners Examining Committee and he is a Member of Fordham University's President's Council and the Advisory Board of Rutgers University's Prudential Center for Business Ethics. Mr. Daleo holds an undergraduate degree from the Fordham University and an MBA in Finance from the City University of New York.Read Full Background




